#IGN #ComixZero #Metroidvania
title: Comix Zero - 26 Minutes of Gameplay

author: IGN
description:
After nine movies featuring demons forcing parents to try and kill their children, demons forcing children to try and kill their parents, nuns trying to kill nuns, goats trying to kill little French girls, and dolls trying to kill... everyone, The Conjuring universe seems to be bringing the hellish case files of Ed & Lorraine Warren to a close with The Conjuring: Last Rites.

The events of The Conjuringverse stretch all the way back to the year 304 AD, and we've updated our timeline to represent the events of every movie in the franchise, from 2013's The Conjuring all the way up to the soon-to-be-released Last Rites... and yes, Father Perez's appearance in both Annabelle and The Curse of La Llorona makes the latter canon in our dead doll eyes!

#IGN #Movies
title: The Conjuring Universe Timeline in Chronological Order (2025 Edition)

author: IGN
description:
Before GTA 6's Lucia and Jason arrive and potentially win our hearts, who is the current number 1 Grand Theft Auto protagonist?

From Tommy Vercetti to GTA 5's Trevor, Michael and Franklin, Grand Theft Auto is stacked with iconic characters we all remember. But which one is the best? Do you prefer Niko Bellic from GTA 4 to GTA 3's Claude? And where does CJ from GTA San Andreas sit? We put all the best Grand Theft Auto characters to the test to finally decide the ultimate ranking. 

Who's the best Grand Theft Auto character of all time? Let's find out!

00:00 - Intro
00:31 - Grand Theft Auto 1 Characters
01:40 - Claude Speed - GTA 2
02:37 - Claude - GTA 3
03:59 - Tommy Vercetti - GTA Vice City
04:47 - Tony Cipriani and Victor Vance
06:58 - Johnny Klebitz - Lost and Damned
08:09 - Michael De Santa - GTA 5

09:59 - Luis Lopez - Ballad of Gay Tony
11:14 - Trevor Phillips - GTA 5
13:02 - Frankin Clinton - GTA 5
14:53 - C.J - San Andreas
16:26 - Niko Be
title: The Best GTA Characters, Ranked

author: IGN
description:
Don't miss the Albion Trailer for Anno 117: Pax Romana, an upcoming historical strategy simulation city-builder developed by Ubisoft Mainz. Players will set out to influence the Roman provinces through the use of strategic economic force, skills of diplomacy, and the might of one of Earth's most powerful countries in modern history. Craft the Roman Empire how you see fit in Anno 117: Pax Romana, launching on November 13 for PlayStation 5 (PS5), Xbox Series X|S, and PC (Steam and Epic Games Store).

#Anno117 #Albion #Gaming
title: Anno 117: Pax Romana - Official Albion Trailer
